WEBVTT

03:09.081 --> 03:10.195
- New patient?
- Yes.

03:10.360 --> 03:13.000
I was referred by my lawyer
about veneers.

03:13.161 --> 03:14.914
You're a new patient. Fill this out...

03:15.082 --> 03:17.721
....so we know who to contact
in case we lose you in the chair.

03:19.804 --> 03:22.160
That was a joke, sweetie.
I was being funny.

03:25.325 --> 03:26.998
Hello.

03:27.166 --> 03:30.716
Mrs. Remar, I'm Dr. Johnson.

03:30.886 --> 03:32.366
Oh, it's Miss Remar.

03:32.527 --> 03:36.078
And I know who you are. I see another
doctor in the building regularly.

03:36.248 --> 03:38.205
I've been on the elevator
with you a few times.

03:38.369 --> 03:40.042
Oh, okay.

03:40.210 --> 03:43.169
You're married?
I never noticed the ring before.

03:43.331 --> 03:46.050
Oh, yes, I am. I'm married.

03:46.211 --> 03:48.773
All right, what are we doing
for you today?

03:49.692 --> 03:51.331
One veneer, is that right?

03:51.493 --> 03:53.883
They told me you don't
usually do just one.

03:54.055 --> 03:56.808
We do whatever's needed.
Allie.

03:57.855 --> 04:00.575
All right. Let's see.

04:01.137 --> 04:03.810
- Now, which one is it?
- I don't know.

04:03.977 --> 04:05.570
You tell me.

04:16.341 --> 04:19.015
So another cutie with a crush, huh?

04:19.821 --> 04:21.177
What is it with you?

04:25.103 --> 04:26.936
So you'll be back next week?

04:27.105 --> 04:30.017
You're gonna schedule Miss Remar
next week for the veneer. Right?

04:30.185 --> 04:32.381
Yeah. I'm gonna clear the
schedule the whole week...

04:32.546 --> 04:34.937
....so that you could be mentally
prepared for it. Okay?

04:35.547 --> 04:37.459
It was so nice to finally meet you.

04:37.628 --> 04:39.937
Oh, yeah. You too.

04:42.230 --> 04:43.982
Okay.

04:44.150 --> 04:45.742
I need the...

04:47.311 --> 04:49.542
Oh, it's my daughters.

04:49.712 --> 04:51.191
I'm gonna need that jacket.

04:54.514 --> 04:57.392
- Okay, you stay, and then I'll reach.
- Sorry.

04:57.554 --> 04:59.510
No, that's fine. I'm minutes away.

05:12.239 --> 05:13.797
Charlie...?

05:14.239 --> 05:16.708
Hey, Charlie! Charlie Fineman!

05:22.683 --> 05:24.320
Charlie!

05:30.685 --> 05:34.394
Charlie. Charlie Fineman.

06:02.535 --> 06:05.572
I'm so sick of your father.

06:05.735 --> 06:07.374
He's in that bed again.

06:07.536 --> 06:10.051
Just as mean and evil as he can be.

06:10.217 --> 06:12.685
Like a pig with a bullet in his head.

06:12.857 --> 06:15.054
You take your walk today, Mom?

06:17.379 --> 06:19.735
I'll take that as a no.

06:24.022 --> 06:25.613
Dad?

06:27.943 --> 06:31.015
I hate this city. I hate this damn city.

06:31.183 --> 06:33.572
I don't know why
you brought us here.

06:34.585 --> 06:37.305
I got the papaya juice you asked for.

06:39.386 --> 06:41.948
Hate this damn city.

06:42.668 --> 06:47.264
And the smell. All that garbage
all up and down the street.

06:47.428 --> 06:49.625
Daddy? I need money for the
dress for the dinner...

06:49.790 --> 06:51.348
....I'm going to with the Jacobsons.

06:51.510 --> 06:52.784
And you'll have to drive me...

06:52.950 --> 06:55.671
....because Mom's gonna be
at Cherie's chorus practise.

06:55.912 --> 06:57.231
Okay.

06:57.393 --> 06:59.189
We have to talk about
getting a cell phone.

06:59.352 --> 07:01.628
This morning, you said
we could talk about it tonight.

07:02.435 --> 07:04.789
I thought we talked about
the cell-phone issue.

07:04.954 --> 07:07.229
But I'm 13 and I still share
with my little sister.

07:07.394 --> 07:09.546
Oh, right. Because you only
need a cell phone...

07:09.716 --> 07:12.675
....if Mommy or Daddy's late...
- I ran into Charlie Fineman today.

07:14.036 --> 07:15.597
Really? How is he?

07:15.759 --> 07:20.274
I don't know. I was in the car
and he was on foot.

07:20.439 --> 07:23.353
He was coming out of a hardware
store. He was carrying paint.

07:23.521 --> 07:25.637
You think he's still practising?

07:27.600 --> 07:29.911
Who's Charlie Fineman, Daddy?

07:30.442 --> 07:33.081
He's an old college friend
of mine, baby.

07:33.243 --> 07:36.043
He was my college
roommate, actually.

07:36.525 --> 07:38.481
I haven't talked to him
in a long, long time.

07:38.805 --> 07:40.874
Is he the one from dental school...

07:41.045 --> 07:45.199
....whose family was on the plane?
Is that Charlie Fineman?

07:46.047 --> 07:47.560
Yeah.

07:47.727 --> 07:49.765
That's Charlie Fineman.

08:06.774 --> 08:10.734
You know, I decided to sign us up
for another photography class.

08:13.015 --> 08:15.895
You did?
You already signed us up?

08:16.057 --> 08:18.696
Yeah, but this time
for the advanced one.

08:18.857 --> 08:21.816
I thought we had fun last quarter,
didn't you?

08:22.900 --> 08:24.252
What, you don't want to?

08:24.419 --> 08:27.093
No, I do. Don't you?

08:27.260 --> 08:28.819
I loved it.

08:28.980 --> 08:30.574
- I had a really good time.
- Yeah.

08:30.742 --> 08:32.059
- Didn't you love it?
- I did.

08:32.222 --> 08:36.615
And now Advanced Photography?
I mean, wow. I'm... Yeah.

08:36.784 --> 08:38.183
Good.

08:39.743 --> 08:40.893
No sugar.

08:41.063 --> 08:43.341
Don't take that to school, okay?

08:43.506 --> 08:46.623
Whole Foods. Whole Foods snacks.

09:01.831 --> 09:03.902
- Hey, Angela.
- Dr. Johnson.

09:04.072 --> 09:06.870
What is it about us always leaving
the building at the same time?

09:07.032 --> 09:08.911
- It's quitting time.
- That's true.

09:09.074 --> 09:11.111
- You good?
- Yeah, I'm good. Thanks.

09:11.275 --> 09:13.994
Good. Let me ask you something.
Most married men have hobbies.

09:14.155 --> 09:15.747
Okay, Alan. Don't do this.
Come on.

09:15.916 --> 09:18.032
- Don't do what?
- We talked about this.

09:18.196 --> 09:21.587
It's not really fair for you
to wait for me out here on the street.

09:21.757 --> 09:24.671
If you wanna make an appointment,
we can make an appointment.

09:24.839 --> 09:26.636
Yeah, I know. But it's a little thing.

09:26.799 --> 09:28.995
Now, you remember the friend
I was asking you about?

09:29.160 --> 09:31.231
The friend who has no friends?
Other than you?

09:31.401 --> 09:33.516
Yeah, him. So he's
a married guy, right?

09:33.680 --> 09:35.912
And he's got a great wife
and the whole nine.

09:36.081 --> 09:40.873
But she will not let him...
I mean, it's like he can't just...

09:41.402 --> 09:42.962
I mean, guys have
guy hobbies, right?

09:43.125 --> 09:45.002
They play poker, they golf,
they do shit.

09:45.165 --> 09:47.474
Okay, you know what? Stop. Stop.

09:47.645 --> 09:49.682
I can't treat you from the lobby
to the car park.

09:49.847 --> 09:53.362
Treat me? I'm not...
I just asked you a question.

09:53.727 --> 09:56.037
- Well, whatever you wanna call it...
- No, you're right.

09:56.208 --> 09:58.279
- It's inappropriate.
- You're right. I get it.

09:58.449 --> 09:59.599
Let me ask you one thing.

09:59.770 --> 10:02.490
I want your opinion
as a woman, Angela.

10:02.651 --> 10:04.004
As a woman.

10:05.052 --> 10:08.044
Look, if I have
this recurring dream where...

10:08.212 --> 10:09.852
....I'm sitting on my couch...

10:10.014 --> 10:13.847
....and it turns into a big vat of rubber,
what is that?

10:15.014 --> 10:18.053
Why don't you let me
refer you to someone else?

10:21.975 --> 10:24.094
Okay. Well...

10:24.258 --> 10:26.772
....I hope it works out for you.

10:27.457 --> 10:30.258
You wait for me enough times
out on the street, though...

10:30.420 --> 10:33.059
....you might owe me
some dental work.

10:33.860 --> 10:35.612
Have a nice day.

10:52.306 --> 10:53.660
Bingo. There we go.

10:53.827 --> 10:56.865
- That was a tough one.
- Okay. Absolutely.

10:57.028 --> 11:00.338
Now it all will fall into place.

11:00.508 --> 11:03.307
Dad, can you take me
to Becky Fishman's?

11:03.469 --> 11:05.062
Sweetie, it's 9:30.

11:05.230 --> 11:07.062
She wants me to spend the night.

11:07.231 --> 11:08.983
Well, Daddy's had
a long day at work...

11:09.151 --> 11:11.462
....and he's finally finding some time
to enjoy himself.

11:11.633 --> 11:12.951
Just have her come over here.

11:13.112 --> 11:15.546
And we can study your
French together.

11:15.712 --> 11:17.785
Oh, you know what?
I'll take her. I'll go.

11:17.955 --> 11:20.628
Babe. We've come this far.
We've been working on this all week.

11:20.794 --> 11:24.107
I know. I'll go. I'll go, and then
I'll just come right back.

11:24.277 --> 11:26.996
Don't be mad if I have this
all done by the time you get back.

11:27.157 --> 11:28.351
Because I'm on a roll here.

11:28.517 --> 11:30.953
You're gonna miss out
on all the action.

11:31.119 --> 11:34.316
Just make sure you
save me some sky, okay?

11:34.479 --> 11:36.071
You know you owe
that child bigtime.

11:36.240 --> 11:38.709
You would've thought she got you
out of traffic school...

11:38.881 --> 11:40.519
....by the look on your face.

11:43.202 --> 11:44.921
Good night, babe.

11:46.203 --> 11:48.034
- Good night.
- Thanks.

11:51.165 --> 11:56.559
Hey, Charlie. Charlie.
Charlie Fineman, hey!

11:57.488 --> 11:59.603
Charlie, stop!

12:02.848 --> 12:05.318
- Hey, Charlie. Hey, man.
- Yeah?

12:05.490 --> 12:08.084
- It's Alan.
- Hey. How are you?

12:08.250 --> 12:11.483
I saw you coming out of a paint store
a couple weeks ago and...

12:11.652 --> 12:13.404
I was screaming for you,
honking the horn.

12:13.572 --> 12:15.881
I stopped the car, jumped out
in traffic. It was crazy.

12:16.052 --> 12:19.444
Then I tried to get in touch with you,
but nobody had any info on you.

12:19.614 --> 12:21.286
Oh, good, good. Very cool.

12:21.454 --> 12:24.254
- How you doing?
- So we know each other?

12:25.096 --> 12:26.973
Are you kidding me?

12:27.136 --> 12:29.775
It's Alan Johnson, Charlie.

12:30.656 --> 12:32.933
We went to dental school together.

12:33.098 --> 12:35.976
Burrows Hall. I was your college
roommate. You don't remember me?

12:36.138 --> 12:38.654
Yeah, very cool. Very cool.

12:38.820 --> 12:42.608
- Good. Good to see you, Burrows.
- It's Johnson.

12:43.542 --> 12:47.251
Charlie, you seriously
don't remember me?

12:48.102 --> 12:50.378
- We were college roommates?
- Yeah.

12:50.743 --> 12:53.417
Yeah, you slept naked most nights.

12:53.584 --> 12:56.896
And you were a sleepwalker.
It was the worst two years of my life.

12:57.906 --> 12:59.226
Hey, are you practising, man?

12:59.387 --> 13:01.901
I tried to get in touch
through the Dental Guild...

13:02.067 --> 13:04.424
I'm practising all the time,
up in the valley.

13:04.589 --> 13:06.864
Took down 12 of
the Colossus so far.

13:07.029 --> 13:10.466
The valley? What is that? Is that
a medical complex or something?

13:10.630 --> 13:13.270
It's more like another dimension.

13:13.750 --> 13:17.665
You take a journey
and discover yourself.

13:18.713 --> 13:21.784
- Hey, man, you wanna go get a drink?
- I can't drink. I can't drink.

13:21.952 --> 13:25.186
I can't drink. I can't drink.

13:25.355 --> 13:26.549
I gotta get going.

13:26.715 --> 13:29.513
Then a coffee or something.
Let's just go get a cup of coffee.

13:29.674 --> 13:34.626
Real quick. I would just love to
catch up with you, man.

13:38.999 --> 13:40.228
Hey, Charlie.

13:48.561 --> 13:49.994
This okay?

13:57.604 --> 13:59.357
You like trivia?

14:01.406 --> 14:03.044
Name the Great Lakes.

14:04.167 --> 14:06.728
The Great Lakes.
Can you name them?

14:10.769 --> 14:12.123
Okay, Michigan is one.

14:12.290 --> 14:15.168
Huron, Ontario, Michigan,
Erie and Superior.

14:15.329 --> 14:16.558
That was an easy one.

14:16.730 --> 14:18.244
That's fifth-grade shit.

14:24.333 --> 14:27.451
So, what have you
been up to lately, Charlie?

14:28.174 --> 14:32.488
I'm stuck between
Pale White and Moon White.

14:32.656 --> 14:35.409
I tried Butterscotch Yellow.

14:35.576 --> 14:37.454
I couldn't live with it.

14:37.617 --> 14:40.974
You painting something?
You're remodelling or?

14:42.538 --> 14:45.259
You were my college roommate.

14:48.500 --> 14:51.220
That was a long time ago.

14:55.303 --> 14:58.774
- A whole other life.
- Oh, yeah. No shit.

15:01.104 --> 15:03.698
It's good to see your face.

15:04.826 --> 15:06.418
Johnson.

15:07.387 --> 15:10.185
Yeah, it's good to
see you too, Charlie.

15:13.989 --> 15:16.105
Yeah. All right.

15:16.269 --> 15:18.705
You gotta take those shoes off.

15:26.273 --> 15:27.262
Thank you.

15:27.433 --> 15:29.663
Great record collection.

15:30.113 --> 15:31.627
Yeah.

15:31.794 --> 15:32.831
I'm happy with it.

15:32.996 --> 15:37.705
- A lot of vinyl.
- Yeah. Over 5500 so far.

15:37.876 --> 15:40.027
It's a work in progress.

15:43.198 --> 15:45.154
Kitchen remodel?

15:47.679 --> 15:48.669
What is this?

15:48.840 --> 15:51.070
"Shadows of the Colossus."

16:14.928 --> 16:17.203
Can I use your bathroom, Charlie?

16:18.329 --> 16:20.207
Oh, in the back.

16:47.058 --> 16:48.935
Nice music room.

17:17.267 --> 17:18.301
Good?

17:18.467 --> 17:19.617
Okay.

17:19.789 --> 17:21.858
There you go, Allie. Thank you.

17:30.551 --> 17:33.830
I'm sorry about the way I behaved
the last time I was here, doctor.

17:33.994 --> 17:36.905
But when I see you in the building,
you always seem very busy.

17:37.073 --> 17:38.713
Preoccupied.

17:38.875 --> 17:42.788
Even when you're with the
other doctors, you seem so solitary.

17:42.995 --> 17:44.906
So alone.

17:45.356 --> 17:48.554
I don't know why, but that seems
very familiar to me.

17:49.438 --> 17:51.109
Yeah.

17:51.277 --> 17:52.553
Well.

17:52.719 --> 17:55.109
I hope you're...

17:56.359 --> 17:59.592
I just thought that if you
wanted me to...

17:59.762 --> 18:01.433
....I would.

18:02.242 --> 18:04.312
With my mouth.

18:04.642 --> 18:06.156
I would.

18:07.884 --> 18:09.681
You could lock that door...

18:09.844 --> 18:11.754
....tell the nurse not to come in.

18:13.206 --> 18:14.878
I'd do it.

18:15.606 --> 18:17.995
I'd enjoy making you happy.

18:36.812 --> 18:38.484
You have to leave.

18:38.652 --> 18:43.809
I have this odd sense of intimacy
towards you. I don't even know why.

18:43.974 --> 18:46.092
I told my shrink, and she
said I should act on it.

18:46.256 --> 18:48.088
Oh, she did?
You need to get a new shrink.

18:48.257 --> 18:50.053
Get several.
And get a new dentist too.

18:50.216 --> 18:52.093
You gotta get out of here,
Miss Remar.

18:52.256 --> 18:55.375
I'm serious. I need you to leave
right now. Please. Go.

18:55.539 --> 18:57.131
Okay.

18:57.298 --> 18:58.812
Come on.

19:00.941 --> 19:02.613
Okay.

19:02.780 --> 19:04.737
The fuck...?

19:05.620 --> 19:08.581
I need you not to reschedule
Miss Remar for anything.

19:08.743 --> 19:10.335
Okay.

19:10.863 --> 19:12.296
Ever again. Nothing.

19:12.463 --> 19:13.454
Okay.

19:13.625 --> 19:15.456
I don't want this woman as a patient.

19:15.625 --> 19:17.980
- Got it. I got it.
- Fine. Thank you.

19:20.106 --> 19:21.540
Excuse me!

19:21.707 --> 19:23.379
Not right now. Hey.
Melanie, call her.

19:23.708 --> 19:26.906
- Miss Remar?
- On the phone, I mean. Don't...

19:28.589 --> 19:31.866
Miss Remar, you need
to find another dentist.

19:32.429 --> 19:33.499
- Excuse me?
- You heard me.

19:33.671 --> 19:35.423
Dr. Johnson don't want you
as a patient...

19:35.591 --> 19:37.344
....neither do any
other doctors here...

19:37.512 --> 19:39.947
....so go somewhere, bury your face
in the phone book...

19:40.113 --> 19:42.787
....and find another dentist, all right?

19:50.276 --> 19:52.267
- "Bury your face in the phone book"?
- Yes.

19:52.876 --> 19:55.756
You have to be bold to make
these kind of people go away.

19:55.918 --> 19:57.874
Thanks for holding.

20:14.324 --> 20:15.359
Can I help you?

20:15.524 --> 20:18.482
I'm just going up to see a friend
of mine, Charlie Fineman.

20:19.524 --> 20:22.279
Nobody by that name
lives here. Sorry.

20:26.767 --> 20:28.838
That's fine. I'll just wait
for the landlord.

20:29.008 --> 20:30.601
That's me.

20:31.129 --> 20:34.281
Landlady.
Adell Modell, landlady from hell.

20:34.450 --> 20:37.089
Oh, well, I'm Alan Johnson.
I'm a friend of Charlie's.

20:37.250 --> 20:39.684
- Sure.
- We went to dental school together...

20:40.091 --> 20:43.324
I was in his apartment the other night.
We were playing...

20:43.493 --> 20:45.244
...."Shadows of the Colossus"
or something.

20:45.412 --> 20:49.090
You were up there in his apartment
the other night? That's a load of crap.

20:49.855 --> 20:51.766
He hasn't had anybody
up there in four years.

20:51.935 --> 20:54.132
Just me, Sugarman the accountant,
the cleaning girl.

20:54.297 --> 20:55.969
He doesn't know
about the cleaning girl.

20:56.137 --> 20:59.254
- I'm not lying to you. I was up there.
- Yeah.

20:59.417 --> 21:01.774
He's remodelling his kitchen.
Now, how would I know that?

21:01.939 --> 21:04.658
He's been remodelling that kitchen
once every couple of months.

21:04.819 --> 21:06.856
That tells me nothing. Go away.

21:07.741 --> 21:09.936
Johnson. Johnson!

21:10.141 --> 21:12.211
- Yo.
- Hey.

21:12.621 --> 21:14.534
Alan!

21:14.703 --> 21:16.740
Alan Johnson.

21:16.904 --> 21:18.621
This is my college roommate.

21:18.783 --> 21:20.934
It's my college roommate.

21:21.105 --> 21:23.460
I used to sleep in the nude.

21:25.905 --> 21:26.976
Check this out.

21:28.787 --> 21:31.221
I got a...
You'll appreciate this.

21:31.387 --> 21:36.304
The Pretenders. It's one of the
great debut albums of all time.

21:36.469 --> 21:38.460
Yeah, that's you.
Terrible taste in music.

21:38.709 --> 21:41.509
No, no, not true. Not true.

21:42.752 --> 21:44.708
Smell these things.

21:45.112 --> 21:48.231
I love the way they smell.
Take a whiff.

21:49.393 --> 21:52.032
Brings back a feeling.
Smells like the late '70s, don't it?

21:52.193 --> 21:56.189
- The early '80s. Yeah.
- Charlie!

21:56.356 --> 21:57.584
Charlie!

21:58.196 --> 22:00.152
It's okay, Charlie.
I'll take care of them.

22:00.316 --> 22:02.274
- Who's that?
- Charlie, we just wanna talk.

22:02.438 --> 22:05.316
- We gotta go. We gotta go.
- What?

22:05.478 --> 22:06.467
Why? Who is that?

22:06.638 --> 22:08.756
Johnson, hop on.
Hop on, Johnson.

22:08.920 --> 22:10.593
- Hop on?
- Get on. Get on. Johnson.

22:10.760 --> 22:12.637
- Who is that?
- Johnson, damn it, get on.

22:12.800 --> 22:15.556
- Just get on the back.
- Wait a minute!

22:17.802 --> 22:20.077
Charlie! Charlie! Bus, Charlie!

22:20.242 --> 22:22.439
Oh, shit! Charlie.

22:22.604 --> 22:25.721
I know, I know. All right.

23:00.815 --> 23:03.377
You're late. They're pissed.

23:03.777 --> 23:07.486
Name the one national
U.S. Monument that's movable.

23:07.658 --> 23:10.890
Suck my ass, retard.
You're late. Get in there.

23:11.059 --> 23:13.448
No. San Francisco cable cars.

23:13.619 --> 23:16.772
Good. I didn't know that one either.
That's a good one.

23:16.941 --> 23:19.136
That's a great one if you ever
wanna stump somebody.

23:41.469 --> 23:44.189
If you guys could not laugh
at anything I say, that'd really...

23:44.350 --> 23:47.739
I'm trying to get my self-esteem
to go to, like, seven percent.

23:50.472 --> 23:52.463
Could I get another Heineken?

23:52.632 --> 23:55.193
- You want another root beer?
