01:40:33.713 --> 01:40:37.261
This is not something that
the state should be deciding upon.

01:40:37.431 --> 01:40:39.549
- Your Honour...
- Shut up.

01:40:44.831 --> 01:40:46.582
I'm serious.

01:40:47.071 --> 01:40:50.222
I want you to shut up, Mr. Fallon.

01:40:50.391 --> 01:40:53.509
This is not going well for you,
you hear me?

01:40:53.672 --> 01:40:55.229
Shut up.

01:40:55.390 --> 01:40:56.585
Yes.

01:40:56.753 --> 01:40:58.023
Shut up.

01:41:02.311 --> 01:41:04.699
Mr. And Mrs. Timpleman...

01:41:06.112 --> 01:41:09.627
....this is very serious stuff
we're talking about here.

01:41:10.390 --> 01:41:11.618
I mean, it's easy to see...

01:41:11.789 --> 01:41:14.749
....that this man is going through
something very profound.

01:41:16.510 --> 01:41:18.101
It's obvious.

01:41:19.351 --> 01:41:22.023
He may need some hospitalisation.

01:41:22.190 --> 01:41:23.703
He may.

01:41:24.270 --> 01:41:26.421
On the other hand...

01:41:26.590 --> 01:41:28.821
....he might just need
to find his own way.

01:41:31.388 --> 01:41:32.983
The fact is...

01:41:33.150 --> 01:41:34.902
....you're correct.

01:41:35.510 --> 01:41:37.625
You are the closest thing
he has to family.

01:41:38.389 --> 01:41:40.984
- Thank you.
- Yes, of course.

01:41:44.589 --> 01:41:46.980
I want you to go home...

01:41:47.591 --> 01:41:50.740
....and think very hard this weekend.

01:41:51.588 --> 01:41:55.139
Because we're all gonna meet
back here on Monday morning...

01:41:55.790 --> 01:41:58.824
....and I'm going to let
the two of you decide.

01:41:59.548 --> 01:42:02.507
I want you to rack your brains.

01:42:03.070 --> 01:42:06.059
I want you to think about what
your little girl would have you do...

01:42:06.229 --> 01:42:08.105
....in this situation.

01:42:11.028 --> 01:42:13.258
And I'm gonna have you
look me straight in the eye...

01:42:13.428 --> 01:42:15.383
....on Monday morning...

01:42:16.348 --> 01:42:17.700
....and tell me whether or not...

01:42:17.867 --> 01:42:21.303
....she would want her man
put away in a place like that.

01:42:24.547 --> 01:42:28.097
You understand what it is
that I am telling you, Mrs. Timpleman?

01:42:29.668 --> 01:42:32.578
The power that I am putting
in your hands.

01:42:33.229 --> 01:42:35.457
Yes. Yes, sir.

01:42:35.948 --> 01:42:37.858
Your Honour, can I just say something?
Let me...

01:42:38.028 --> 01:42:39.299
What is his name?

01:42:40.988 --> 01:42:43.023
Bryan Sugarman. Bryan Sugarman.

01:42:44.825 --> 01:42:46.224
Monday morning.

01:42:46.385 --> 01:42:48.025
Ten-thirty.

01:42:48.746 --> 01:42:51.055
Don't bring Sugarman.

01:42:54.145 --> 01:42:56.661
Is Dr. Johnson coming out?

01:42:56.825 --> 01:42:59.737
He's inside with the judge.

01:43:02.106 --> 01:43:03.300
Can I sit down?

01:43:04.865 --> 01:43:07.380
Charlie, can Donna sit down?

01:43:07.544 --> 01:43:10.742
She really wanted to come
to your hearing today to support you.

01:43:12.024 --> 01:43:14.062
- Here?
- Yeah.

01:43:14.905 --> 01:43:16.100
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

01:43:16.625 --> 01:43:19.139
On your side. She can sit
on your side, though. All right?

01:43:29.306 --> 01:43:32.660
I don't know how they can't see
that he's just got a broken heart.

01:43:32.822 --> 01:43:35.976
It's so broken, his poor heart.

01:43:43.264 --> 01:43:44.252
It's okay.

01:44:07.823 --> 01:44:11.179
I don't need to talk about her
or look at pictures...

01:44:11.342 --> 01:44:14.699
....because the truth is,
a lot of times, I see her...

01:44:14.863 --> 01:44:16.773
....on the street.

01:44:17.742 --> 01:44:21.655
I walk down the street,
I see her in someone else's face...

01:44:21.822 --> 01:44:24.814
....clearer than any of the pictures
you carry with you.

01:44:25.780 --> 01:44:27.899
I get that you're in pain.

01:44:28.062 --> 01:44:30.416
But you got each other.

01:44:31.181 --> 01:44:33.136
You got each other...

01:44:33.300 --> 01:44:36.500
....and I'm the one who's gotta
see her and the girls all the time.

01:44:36.661 --> 01:44:39.049
Everywhere I go.

01:44:41.661 --> 01:44:43.698
I even see the dog.

01:44:44.662 --> 01:44:47.302
That's how fucked up I still am.

01:44:47.463 --> 01:44:50.897
I look at a German shepherd,
I see our goddamn poodle.

01:44:56.622 --> 01:44:58.133
All right.

01:45:03.181 --> 01:45:04.694
All right.

01:45:42.139 --> 01:45:43.254
What is this?

01:45:43.420 --> 01:45:47.090
He's gone.
The movers finished up an hour ago.

01:45:47.257 --> 01:45:49.772
Didn't even leave a forwarding.

01:45:52.299 --> 01:45:54.332
He just left this.

01:45:55.097 --> 01:45:58.089
He said that this
was to be for you, Ginger.

01:46:05.698 --> 01:46:08.165
Listen, I know
you've both been through hell...

01:46:08.338 --> 01:46:11.373
....but shouldn't you
just leave him alone?

01:46:12.736 --> 01:46:14.374
We just wanna be part of his life.

01:46:14.536 --> 01:46:17.415
No, I know. I understand,
but it's not an option right now.

01:46:20.256 --> 01:46:22.007
Monday morning,
you need to go in there...

01:46:22.177 --> 01:46:24.372
....and just call off the dogs.

01:46:39.614 --> 01:46:41.127
Okay.

01:46:43.296 --> 01:46:44.933
You take care, Adell.

01:46:45.097 --> 01:46:47.972
Thank you for taking care of Charlie.

01:46:48.136 --> 01:46:49.615
Thanks.

01:46:54.414 --> 01:46:57.055
- When did he redo the kitchen?
- Oh, God, the kitchen.

01:46:57.216 --> 01:47:00.011
Sixteen thousand times
he did the kitchen.

01:47:00.895 --> 01:47:02.805
It's beautiful.

01:47:03.776 --> 01:47:06.970
The girls would love the colour.
They would love this look.

01:47:10.055 --> 01:47:12.205
It's a kitchen, sweetie.

01:47:12.775 --> 01:47:14.253
Come on.

01:47:34.972 --> 01:47:37.124
Can you sign off for me?

01:47:41.573 --> 01:47:42.562
- Hey.
- Thanks.

01:47:42.733 --> 01:47:45.884
This is the last of it. I got a pizza
coming. Could you just send it up?

01:47:46.611 --> 01:47:48.569
Yeah, yeah, we'll send it up.

01:48:02.172 --> 01:48:03.845
You're up.

01:48:04.852 --> 01:48:05.842
Wanna go?

01:48:06.012 --> 01:48:08.002
No, no, no. I gotta...

01:48:08.812 --> 01:48:10.848
....get back to your spot
and get my car.

01:48:11.012 --> 01:48:13.524
I'll come and hang out with you
tomorrow for lunch.

01:48:22.611 --> 01:48:25.569
- Hi.
- Hi. Come on in.

01:48:29.772 --> 01:48:33.365
- Anyone order pizza?
- This is the place. Here, I'll take it.

01:48:33.529 --> 01:48:35.202
Come on in.

01:48:37.411 --> 01:48:38.730
Come on in.

01:48:40.128 --> 01:48:42.247
- I'm gonna go.
- Yeah, I think it's okay.

01:48:45.290 --> 01:48:48.599
- Hi.
- Hey.

01:48:50.850 --> 01:48:52.442
Hey, Charlie...

01:48:53.648 --> 01:48:57.121
....you don't mind if Donna stays
and has some pizza, right?

01:48:59.689 --> 01:49:02.410
Oh, yeah, she can stay.

01:49:04.090 --> 01:49:07.443
- There's some plates in the kitchen.
- Thank you, Dr. Johnson.

01:49:07.848 --> 01:49:09.282
For everything.

01:49:13.009 --> 01:49:13.995
Okay.

01:49:22.728 --> 01:49:26.005
I'm gonna take off and I'll catch you
tomorrow, all right, buddy?

01:49:26.169 --> 01:49:27.725
All right, go ahead. You're up.

01:49:27.887 --> 01:49:30.800
- I'm up? I told you, I gotta go...
- You said you wanted to go again.

01:49:30.968 --> 01:49:33.435
I thought you said that.
Don't you wanna go?

01:49:33.607 --> 01:49:36.167
You said you wanted to
take another shot and stick around.

01:49:36.327 --> 01:49:37.761
Yep, that's what I said.

01:49:54.406 --> 01:49:56.159
"Shadows of the Colossus."

01:50:30.886 --> 01:50:33.639
- Hey.
- Hey.

01:50:33.804 --> 01:50:36.317
Where are you?
Did you pick the girls up yet?

01:50:36.484 --> 01:50:38.078
Going right now.

01:50:38.726 --> 01:50:39.918
What are you doing?

01:50:40.085 --> 01:50:41.995
What do you think I'm doing?
Cooking dinner.

01:50:45.885 --> 01:50:48.522
Janeane, I gotta tell you
something, babe.

01:50:50.604 --> 01:50:54.722
I don't know how I got to the place
where I'm not letting you in...

01:50:54.883 --> 01:50:57.193
....but you're right, I'm not.

01:50:57.365 --> 01:50:59.434
And that's wrong.
I gotta open up to you.

01:51:00.124 --> 01:51:02.078
Because I don't wanna be
that guy, baby.

01:51:02.243 --> 01:51:04.632
I don't wanna be that guy.

01:51:05.883 --> 01:51:09.352
I don't know if anything I said
even makes any sense, but...

01:51:19.043 --> 01:51:20.795
Alan, just come home. I love you.

01:51:20.961 --> 01:51:23.524
I know I probably don't
tell you that enough, but I do.

01:51:24.444 --> 01:51:26.399
I love you.

01:51:26.883 --> 01:51:29.521
Can you just pick the girls up
and come home?

01:51:31.123 --> 01:51:33.114
I love you too.

01:51:33.284 --> 01:51:35.920
I'll be home in a minute, okay?

01:51:39.242 --> 01:51:40.881
You guys left this.

01:51:41.043 --> 01:51:43.762
Don't leave stuff laying around.
I mean it.

01:51:44.402 --> 01:51:48.077
Hey. No, no, no, Kemp.
Take this back upstairs. Kemp.

01:52:25.506 --> 01:52:37.690
THE END
